						               													<description>On September 16, 1955, the coup d'&amp;eacute;tat of the Fusiladora Revolution took place against the constitutional government of General Juan Domingo Per&amp;oacute;n, after which he began a long exile of 18 years. The last ten will take place at Quinta 17 de Octubre, located in the small town of Puerta de Hierro, on the outskirts of Madrid, Spain. From there, he will begin to navigate a political labyrinth of intrigues, loyalties, and betrayals that will finally lead him to return triumphantly to the country in 1972 and, the following year, to be elected constitutional president of Argentina for the third time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECTIVE OF THE GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game takes historical facts as its basis and translates them into the cards of the notable personalities of that turbulent time, which players must secretly handle to obtain a specified number of legitimation tokens, thus achieving ultimate victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Throughout the game, each player will keep a secret card in his hand (which could vary on his turn) and that represents his contact of influence and the one who will be the one to carry his message to General Per&amp;oacute;n. You will want to make sure that the person closest to the General has the message from him at the end of the day, so that it can be delivered with priority.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game takes place in rounds that ends when the insert deck is exhausted at the end of a turn, or if all the players except one are eliminated from it. In the first case, the player with the most influence wins a standing token; in the second case, the one left standing wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A player is declared the winner of the game after collecting a certain number of influence tokens, based on the number of players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
